      <data key="d1">"Territorial Behavior describes the actions taken by the Fringe Head and Octopus to defend their respective spaces against competition from one another."&lt;SEP&gt;"Territorial Behavior describes the actions taken by zebras, particularly males, to establish and defend their mating and feeding areas."&lt;SEP&gt;"Territorial Behavior encompasses the aggressive actions and social dynamics exhibited by the langurs as they establish dominance and protect their assets."</data>
