    <node id="&quot;ROCKY TERRAIN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Rocky Terrain describes the rugged landscape that serves as habitat for the musk oxen and wolves, influencing their behavior and interactions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Rocky Terrain is a geographic feature seen in the savannah where the Lioness and her cub are depicted, representing the diverse environment both predators and prey inhabit."&lt;SEP&gt;"Rocky Terrain is a specific habitat featured in the video, providing a natural environment for crabs to navigate and seek shelter."&lt;SEP&gt;"Rocky Terrain is a type of physical geography that influences the habitat and behavior of species like Ibex, adapted to climb and navigate steep areas."&lt;SEP&gt;"Rocky Terrain is the natural setting where these animals interact, characterized by its uneven surface and challenging conditions for life."&lt;SEP&gt;"Rocky Terrain refers to the harsh landscape depicted in the video, which influences the behavior and survival tactics of the animals within it."&lt;SEP&gt;"Rocky Terrain represents the arid and rugged landscape where langurs, baboons, and guanacos are observed, offering a challenging environment for these animals."&lt;SEP&gt;"Rocky terrain is a prominent feature of the coastal ecosystem, providing habitats for various marine species such as crabs and eels."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Rocky Terrain serves as a dry and challenging landscape where various animal interactions and behaviors are observed."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-75ee22de4c8585581875fd638e5b0846&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-392cb505e2c4438b46864f8bfdf3274f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8fb8ec354a08f37ba92e9727af6e50f0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9b81e0839263410236581cf07da3ab84&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-76845fbe1d0e2c45e61cb26e36b6706a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d748003702834ba98c3448df5948c32b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-94260cdac686d7ce14d49d658ccb88e5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7fe346b2d7e7742f1934751d542dbf63&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c3786c86ecb5303fd32a241671e2d7a0</data>
    </node>
