    <node id="&quot;NATURAL HABITAT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Natural Habitat encompasses environments like beaches and ocean surfaces where animals like birds and dolphins interact and thrive."&lt;SEP&gt;"Natural Habitat encompasses the ecosystems that support the lives of both ostriches and cheetahs, providing the necessary resources for their survival."&lt;SEP&gt;"Natural Habitat encompasses the environments in which penguins, seals, and other marine life exist, highlighting the interaction between species."&lt;SEP&gt;"Natural Habitat refers to the areas where guanacos thrive, providing insights into their behavior and ecological interactions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Natural Habitat refers to the environment in which ants live and operate, providing resources and space for their activities and social interactions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Natural Habitat refers to the environment in which the ants and other species reside, highlighting the ecological context that supports various interactions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Natural Habitat refers to the environment in which the otters and reptiles reside and interact, which includes both water bodies and surrounding foliage, framing their survival challenges."&lt;SEP&gt;"Natural Habitat refers to the environment in which various species, such as the tiger and wild boar, live, thrive, and interact with one another."&lt;SEP&gt;"Natural Habitat refers to the environment where an animal lives and thrives, characterized by specific climatic and geographical conditions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Natural Habitat refers to the environment where wild animals, such as lions and hyenas, live and thrive, shaped by climate and landscape conditions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Natural Habitat refers to the environment where zebras thrive and exhibit their natural behaviors, emphasizing the importance of unspoiled ecosystems for their survival."&lt;SEP&gt;"Natural Habitat refers to the lush environments where wildlife, such as chimpanzees and black bears, thrive, showcasing rich biodiversity and the natural behaviors of the species residing within."&lt;SEP&gt;"Natural Habitat refers to the serene environment where hippos and other wildlife live, characterized by calm waters and lush greenery."&lt;SEP&gt;"Natural Habitat represents the serene environment where hippos live and interact, showcasing the ecosystem and their behaviors."&lt;SEP&gt;"Natural Habitat signifies the environments where species like the Ibex and Cheetah flourish, shaped by various ecological factors."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Natural Habitat contextually includes the rich biodiversity of the Jungle, influencing the behaviors of species."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-78ca2dbb111b4b4d4ea43089a2f59d3a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-75ee22de4c8585581875fd638e5b0846&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4ae046d5bbf8f2ea23d0b2a28a80ad4f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a08cd8007acb6f672bd7b0703b7b4d6a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2bc15cf28b425f60295fc9985a4342b4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-32b9985870a633a0e3aadbceb1f9f153&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30042dd8677e949d62274cf1085c26f0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-353dc7023982d7520f78214371fdb5fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e22c5cf5deaee06d3348e54579d0515&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ede3fb638cbde2cc8057e9ad46a1b994&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e50d0acf91551b0b60eba4d131f2af55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-380c1bc50d13674d542887bba78aeb1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-493b89daf392286ffddf2abf03f4d02a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef0b272f4d7e8a853190fd4a1673117e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f42c1f92837671f9cdc536feeaf5e245&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-70388b4cfa1bd5c915c48752680ef325</data>
    </node>
