    <node id="&quot;ENVIRONMENTAL ADAPTATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Environmental Adaptation is the process by which species evolve behaviors and physical traits to survive in their specific habitats."&lt;SEP&gt;"Environmental Adaptation refers to the guanaco's ability to adjust to various conditions in its habitat, such as semi-arid terrain and predator presence."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2bc15cf28b425f60295fc9985a4342b4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-75ee22de4c8585581875fd638e5b0846</data>
