    <node id="&quot;MONITOR LIZARD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ANIMAL"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Monitor Lizard, possibly a lace monitor or goanna, is shown displaying aggressive behavior as it attempts to confront the possum, highlighting its predatory nature."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0fa7e68b98ad851a5f1ad7067bdfb774</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TREE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Tree serves as the habitat for both the Water Lizard and the Possum, providing a nesting site and a setting for the predatory interaction."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Tree serves as the habitat for the possum and the monitor lizard, playing a crucial role as a setting for the impending confrontation and escape."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e5ec702f1741aa9901cb587276f06451&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0fa7e68b98ad851a5f1ad7067bdfb774</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SNAKE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Snake is a predator that appears in the scene, attempting to catch the Monitor Lizard as it climbs the tree, showcasing the natural dynamics of predator-prey interactions."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Snake is a reptile that shares the coastal environment with marine iguanas, exhibiting predatory behavior and the ability to navigate sandy and rocky terrains."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Snake is highlighted in the video for its intricate patterns and movement, showcasing the complexity of wildlife interactions in its habitat."&lt;SEP&gt;"The snake is a reptile featured prominently in the video, exhibiting predatory instincts and interactions with hatchlings."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-0a87cc8fa42efdb394c66837dacbb072&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-883b831036b18b6c493a41889aa63b8f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d748003702834ba98c3448df5948c32b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0fa7e68b98ad851a5f1ad7067bdfb774</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WATER LIZARD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ANIMAL"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Water Lizard is depicted as a predator engaged in a dramatic encounter, demonstrating its adept hunting skills by lunging into a possum's nest to capture baby possums."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Water Lizard is referenced as a possible identification for the Monitor Lizard, indicating its role in the ecosystem as a predator."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e5ec702f1741aa9901cb587276f06451&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0fa7e68b98ad851a5f1ad7067bdfb774</data>
    </node>
