    <node id="&quot;BISON&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Bison are large herbivores known for their social structure and capability to thrive in cold climates, often seen grazing in herds."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bison are large herbivores that are shown engaging in aggressive reactions, demonstrating their social behavior and territorial nature within their natural habitat."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bison are large herbivorous animals that form herds and are depicted in a struggle for survival against wolves in a snowy environment."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bison are large herbivorous mammals known for their robust bodies and distinctive horns, commonly found in herds in the grasslands of Yellowstone Valley during mating season."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bison are large mammals native to North America, often seen in herds, characterized by their massive size and thick fur which provides insulation in cold environments."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bison are large mammals recognized as powerful grazers, often featured as formidable prey in predator hunting scenarios."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bison are large, sturdy animals recognized for their significant role in various ecosystems, often found grazing in meadows."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bison are robust animals that traverse arid landscapes, seeking food or water. Their herd dynamics are often influenced by environmental factors."</data>
